# Milestone 1 Rules – LinkedIn Pipeline MVP

Parent roadmap section: **Milestone 1** in `docs/roadmap.md`

## Scope (must-have)
- Implement `scripts/fetch-linkedin.js` to scrape public profile HTML.
- Add CI step to run the script; builds fail on non-zero exit.
- Produce `data/auto/linkedin.json` with structure:
  ```jsonc
  {
    "positions": [
      { "title": "", "company": "", "start": "YYYY-MM", "end": "YYYY-MM|null", "summary": "" }
    ],
    "education": [
      { "school": "", "degree": "", "start": "YYYY", "end": "YYYY|null" }
    ],
    "skills": ["TypeScript", "Genomics", …]
  }
  ```
- Replace placeholder `ExperienceTimeline.astro` to visualise positions.
- Component must accept prop `max_items` (default 3) to limit items.
- Update README with LinkedIn slug instructions.

## Out of scope
- AI summarisation (belongs to Milestone 2).
- Styling overhaul (belongs to Milestone 3).

## Acceptance criteria
- `npm run dev` with a valid LinkedIn slug displays a timeline.
- GitHub Actions workflow passes and deploys JSON in the artifact.
- All Milestone 1 boxes in `docs/roadmap.md` are ticked.
